@100500  = ~Theft from the Flaming Fist Storage Tent~

@100501  = ~Theft from the Flaming Fist Storage Tent

A Flaming Fist Scout asked me - admittedly very friendly - to go talk to Belegarm about a theft out of the storage tent.~
@100502  = ~Theft from the Flaming Fist Storage Tent

I decided I can't be bothered with the ham thief. I'm sure Belegarm has enough support by the soldiers, and since I wasn't suspected of taking it, helping to look for it or the thief seemed like a waste of time.~
@100503  = ~Theft from the Flaming Fist Storage Tent

I suggested to help search for the ham thief out of the storage tent by letting Grey sniff for the special herb mixture. Belegarm gave me the cloth the ham was wrapped in before it was hung up, it should still smell of the special herb mixture the ham was smoked with. If anyone has a slice of the ham with them, or if it is still somewhere in the tents, I am sure Grey will find it. The problem is, that I have no idea where to look for it - I guess I just need to try my luck. Although we suspect it was refugees who took it, I guess searching around the tents will be a good start.~
@100504  = ~Theft from the Flaming Fist Storage Tent

A dog loving boy handed Grey an admittingly well-looking slice of ham. Grey sniffed it intensely - could it be from the stolen ham Belegarm is looking for? The boy is gone, unfortunately, so I can't ask him where he got it from. I won't find him again in this crowd.~
@100505  = ~Theft from the Flaming Fist Storage Tent

There is no trace of the ham to be found, at least not here. We'll have to see whether more pieces of it will turn up. With the size of that hock, I am sure there will be - question is where.~
@100506  = ~Theft from the Flaming Fist Storage Tent

Alright, seems some wit dressed as a Flaming Fist soldier handed out pieces of ham, telling it's from the city of Baldur's Gate. Maybe I should investigate this. It might be the missing ham that was stolen from the storage tent.~
@100507  = ~Theft from the Flaming Fist Storage Tent

Belegarm, quartermaster of Flaming Fist forces doesn't know anything about extra ham being handed out. Well - officially, that is. He did hear about slices being handed out *pretending* to be from the city's authorities, though.~
@100508  = ~Theft from the Flaming Fist Storage Tent

A refugee just thanked me for ham that was handed to him for free as a treat from Baldur's Gate's noble families, apparently. As noble as this sounds, I should check with Belegarm whether this is real - if not, then I sense a great misunderstanding here - to say the least. Could this be pieces of his missing ham resurfacing?~
@100509  = ~Theft from the Flaming Fist Storage Tent

The soldier handing out ham was last seen in the west of the camp, near the storage tents.~
@100510  = ~Theft from the Flaming Fist Storage Tent

Would you look at that. I just "found" delicious ham on Lester, a Flaming Fist Mercenary. He is in the western part of the camp, between the tents. Maybe I should interrogate him about his connection to the stolen ham a bit more thoroughly.~
@100511  = ~Theft from the Flaming Fist Storage Tent

Well, how very generous. I found the ham thief and brought him in - a soldier, no less - and got a bag with ham pieces as a reward. Well, I guess there wasn't more to be expected from Belegarm with Grey near his tent, now was there.~
@100512  = ~Theft from the Flaming Fist Storage Tent

I found the ham thief and let him go. He was a soldier, no less.~
@100513  = ~Theft from the Flaming Fist Storage Tent

Well, things progressed and I didn't have time to deal with finding the thief. I guess whoever took the hock is of no importance now - and the ham long gone.~
@100514  = ~Theft from the Flaming Fist Storage Tent

Waizahb gave me a hint about a refugee called Scald you asked her to fence greater amounts of food. She doesn't know whether it's (the) ham, but I guess it wouldn't hurt to ask. He should be somewhere between the rows of tents.~
/* journal entry for crossmod with Husam NPC */
@100515  = ~Theft from the Flaming Fist Storage Tent

Husam found who stole the ham from Belegarm's tent - appartently, it's a Flaming Fist Mercenary called Lester. He is in the western part of the camp, between the tents. Maybe I should interrogate him about his connection to the stolen ham a bit more thoroughly.~